It is classified as a benign eccrine neoplasm, a melanocytic nevus, and an eccrine sweat gland hamartoma, and is noted for being rare.

column4: pending final vetting has definition a All definitions, placement in the asserted IS_A hierarchy and required minimal metadata are complete. The class is awaiting a final review by someone other than the term editor..

column4: defined class has definition a A defined class is a class that is defined by a set of logically necessary and sufficient conditions but is not a universal.
column5: A defined class is a class that is specified by a set of logically necessary and sufficient conditions but is not universal.

column4: named class expression has definition a A named class expression is a logical expression that is given a name. The name can be used in place of the expression..
column5: A named class expression is a logical expression given a name, which can be used as a substitute for the expression.

column4: organizational term has definition a Term created to ease viewing/sort terms for development purpose, and will not be included in a release.
column5: An organizational term is defined as a term created to facilitate the viewing and sorting of terms for development purposes, and it will not be included in a release.

column4: metadata incomplete has definition a Class is being worked on; however, the metadata (including definition) are not complete or sufficiently clear to the branch editors..
column5: The definition and metadata for a Class are still being developed and are not yet complete or clear enough for the branch editors to use effectively.

column4: uncurated has definition a Nothing done yet beyond assigning a unique class ID and proposing a preferred term..
column5: "Uncurated" refers to a state where nothing has been done yet beyond assigning a unique class ID and proposing a preferred term.

column4: metadata complete has definition a Class has all its metadata, but is either not guaranteed to be in its final location in the asserted IS_A hierarchy or refers to another class that is not complete..
column5: A class with complete metadata has its definition and all associated metadata. However, it may not be in its final position within the asserted IS_A hierarchy or it might refer to another class that is not yet complete.

column4: failed exploratory term has definition a The term was used in an attempt to structure part of the ontology but in retrospect failed to do a good job.
column5: The term "failed exploratory term" refers to an attempt to structure part of the ontology, but in hindsight, it did not succeed in doing a good job.

column4: requires discussion has definition a A term that is metadata complete, has been reviewed, and problems have been identified that require discussion before release. Such a term requires editor note(s) to identify the outstanding issues..
column5: A term that requires discussion is defined as metadata complete, reviewed, and has identified problems that need to be addressed before release. Such a term requires editor notes to highlight the outstanding issues.

column4: ready for release has definition a Class has undergone final review, is ready for use, and will be included in the next release. Any class lacking "ready_for_release" should be considered likely to change place in hierarchy, have its definition refined, or be obsoleted in the next release. Those classes deemed "ready_for_release" will also derived from a chain of ancestor classes that are also "ready_for_release.".
column5: A class marked as "ready for release" has undergone final review, is ready for use, and will be included in the next release. Any class without this status is likely to change its place in the hierarchy, have its definition refined, or be obsoleted in the upcoming release. Additionally, classes marked as "ready for release" will derive from a chain of ancestor classes that are also marked as "ready for release."

column4: to be replaced with external ontology term has definition a Terms with this status should eventually replaced with a term from another ontology..
column5: Terms with this status should eventually be replaced with a term from another ontology.
